{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, Dewey (1981) explicitly discussed the importance of personal evaluations (including praise, blame, encouragement, condemnation, rewards, and punishments) in human morality.",
    "Analogously, evaluations, rewards, and penalties are crucial to reinforcement learning in LLMs.",
    "In recent years, AI alignment has garnered significant attention and became a goal pursued by numerous research institutions and technology companies.",
    "With RLHF being a significant approach employed by OpenAI to achieve AI alignment, scientists have also made quite a lot of attempts in this area over the past few years (Christiano et al., 2018; Gabriel, 2020; Yuan et al., 2022).",
    "So, how does the moral evolution of LLMs contribute to AI alignment?"
  ]
}